{"title_page": "Bijan Namdar Zangeneh", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox President \n| name         = Bijan Namdar Zangeneh\n| image        = Bijan Namdar Zangeneh 2019 (cropped).jpg\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1952|9|21|df=y}}<ref>[https://www.opec.org/opec_web/static_files_project/media/downloads/about_us/IR%20Iran.pdf Eng. Bijan Namdar Zanganeh]</ref>\n| birth_place  = [[Kermanshah]], [[Iran]]\n| order        = [[Ministry of Petroleum (Iran)|Minister of Petroleum]]\n| term_start   = 15 August 2013\n| term_end     = \n| deputy       = [[Kazem Vaziri Hamaneh]]<br>[[Marzieh Shah-Daei]]\n| president    = [[Hassan Rouhani]]\n| predecessor  = [[Rostam Ghasemi]]\n| order2       = \n| term_start2  = 14 August 1997\n| term_end2    = 7 August 2005\n| president2   = [[Mohammad Khatami]]\n| predecessor2 = [[Gholam Reza Aghazadeh]]\n| successor2   = [[Kazem Vaziri Hamane]]\n| order3       = [[Ministry of Energy (Iran)|Minister of Energy]]\n| term_start3  = 2 September 1988\n| term_end3    = 14 August 1997\n| president3   = [[Ali Khamenei]]<br>[[Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani]]\n| primeminister3 = [[Mir-Hossein Mousavi]]\n| predecessor3 = [[Abolhassan Khamoushi]] {{small|(Acting)}}\n| successor3   = [[Habibollah Bitaraf]]\n| order4       = [[Jihad of Construction|Minister of Jihad of Construction]]\n| term_start4  = 14 November 1983\n| term_end4    = 2 September 1988\n| president4   = [[Ali Khamenei]]\n| primeminister4 = [[Mir-Hossein Mousavi]]\n| predecessor4 = ''Office established''\n| successor4   = [[Gholamreza Forouzesh]]\n| party        = [[Executives of Construction Party]]\n| alma_mater   = [[University of Tehran]] \n| occupation   = \n| spouse       = \n| children     = 4<ref>[http://www.tasnimnews.com/fa/news/1392/05/14/111787/%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%82-%D9%88-%DA%A9%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%87-%D8%A8%DB%8C%DA%98%D9%86-%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D8%B2%D9%86%DA%AF%D9%86%D9%87-%DA%A9%D9%87-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B2-%DA%AF%D8%B0%D8%B4%D8%AA%D9%87-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%84%D8%B3-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF \u0633\u0648\u0627\u0628\u0642 \u0648 \u06a9\u0627\u0631\u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647 \"\u0628\u06cc\u0698\u0646 \u0646\u0627\u0645\u062f\u0627\u0631 \u0632\u0646\u06af\u0646\u0647\" \u06a9\u0647 \u0631\u0648\u062d\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u0631\u0648\u0632 \u06af\u0630\u0634\u062a\u0647 \u0628\u0647 \u0645\u062c\u0644\u0633 \u062f\u0627\u062f ]</ref>\n| signature    = Bijan Namdar Zanganeh signature.svg\n| signature_alt= \n}}\n'''Bijan Namdar Zangeneh''' ({{lang-fa|\u0628\u064a\u0698\u0646 \u0646\u0627\u0645\u062f\u0627\u0631 \u0632\u0646\u06af\u0646\u0647}}; born 21 September 1952) is an [[Iranian peoples|Iranian]] politician, who served as minister at different cabinets after the Islamic Revolution for 32 years. He has been serving as oil minister since 15 August 2013 in [[Government of Hassan Rouhani (2013\u2013present)|the cabinet]] led by [[Hassan Rouhani]].\n\n==Early life and education==\nZangeneh was born to a Kurdish family in [[Kermanshah]] in 1952.<ref>http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iran/21082017</ref> He spent his early school years in his hometown before moving to [[Tehran]] where he received his high school diploma. He received his MSc in civil engineering from the [[University of Tehran]] in 1977 and then became a Civil Engineering professor at [[K. N. Toosi University of Technology]] until his retirement in 2006.<ref>http://dolat.ir/detail/230025 \u062e\u0644\u0627\u0635\u0647 \u0627\u06cc \u0627\u0632 \u0633\u0648\u0627\u0628\u0642 \u0639\u0644\u0645\u06cc \u060c\u0641\u0631\u0647\u0646\u06af\u06cc \u060c\u0633\u06cc\u0627\u0633\u06cc \u0648 \u0627\u062c\u0631\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u0648\u0632\u06cc\u0631\u0646\u0641\u062a</ref>\n\n==Career and activities==\n[[File:Ali Khamenei visit Karkheh Dam (5).jpg|thumb|left|Namdar Zanganeh (right) as minister of energy  with [[Ali Khamenei]], visiting [[Karkheh Dam]], 14 March 1997.]]\nFollowing the [[1979 revolution]], Zangeneh was appointed deputy for the minister of culture and Islamic guidance in 1980.<ref name=sara>{{cite web|title=Iran's Oil Minister Confronts Sanctions|url=http://www.atlanticcouncil.org/publications/articles/iran-s-oil-minister-confronts-sanctions|publisher=Atlantic Council|accessdate=13 September 2013|author=Sara Vakhshouri |date=21 August 2013}}</ref> In 1983, he was made minister of construction jihad.<ref name=sara /> He was appointed minister of energy in the government of [[Mir-Hossein Mousavi]] in 1988.<ref name=sara /> He also served as the energy minister in [[Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani]]'s cabinet<ref name=cabinet>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/08/21/world/iranian-parliament-approves-moderate-president-s-new-cabinet.html|title=Iranian Parliament Approves Moderate President's New Cabinet|accessdate=24 January 2010|date=21 August 1997|work=The New York Times}}</ref> and made massive efforts for reconstruction and rehabilitation of the country's water and electricity industry in the aftermath of the 1980\u20131988 [[Iran\u2013Iraq War]] and the damages caused to the industry in the Iraqi attacks. He was the minister of petroleum in [[Mohammad Khatami]]'s cabinet.<ref name=cabinet /> Zangeneh was replaced by [[Kazem Vaziri Hamane]] in the post on 29 August 2005 as appointed by President [[Mahmoud Ahmadinejad]].<ref name=sara />\n\nHe was appointed as a member of the [[Expediency Council]] by the [[Supreme Leader]], [[Ayatollah Ali Khamenei]], in 1996. He taught at several universities and academic centers; but he was basically a faculty member at [[K. N. Toosi University of Technology]].\n\nIn early August 2013, Zangeneh was nominated as the petroleum minister by President Rouhani and was confirmed on 15 August.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kamali Dehghan|first=Saeed|title=Iran's parliament approves 15 of Hassan Rouhani's 18 cabinet ministers|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/aug/15/iran-middleeast|accessdate=15 August 2013|newspaper=The Guardian|date=15 August 2013}}</ref> On 21 August Zanganeh was named as the head of [[Gas Exporting Countries Forum]] (GECF) for 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Iran's Oil Minister Appointed GECF Head|url=http://www.mees.com/en/articles/8276-irans-oil-minister-apointed-gecf-head|accessdate=13 September 2013|work=Mees|date=21 August 2013|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130913153736/http://www.mees.com/en/articles/8276-irans-oil-minister-apointed-gecf-head|archivedate=13 September 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Kazem Vaziri Hamaneh was appointed as Zangeneh's deputy on 3 September.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vaziri-Hamaneh appointed as Iran's deputy oil minister|url=http://www.tehrantimes.com/economy-and-business/110477-vaziri-hamaneh-appointed-as-irans-deputy-oil-minister-|accessdate=13 September 2013|newspaper=Tehran Times|date=3 September 2013|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130913150049/http://www.tehrantimes.com/economy-and-business/110477-vaziri-hamaneh-appointed-as-irans-deputy-oil-minister-|archivedate=13 September 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Bijan Namdar Zanganeh}}\n{{Portal|Iran|Politics|Biography}}\n{{s-start}} \n{{s-off}}\n{{succession box|before=Position established|title=[[Cabinet of Iran|Minister of Agriculture]]|years=1983\u20131988|after=Gholamreza Forouzesh}}\n{{succession box|before=Mohammad-Taqi Banqi|title=[[Cabinet of Iran|Minister of Energy]]|years=1988\u20131997|after=[[Habibollah Bitaraf]]}}\n{{succession box|before=[[Gholam Reza Aghazadeh]]|title=[[Ministry of Petroleum (Iran)|Minister of Petroleum]]|years=1997\u20132005|after=[[Kazem Vaziri Hamane]]}}\n{{succession box|before=[[Rostam Ghasemi]]|title=[[Ministry of Petroleum (Iran)|Minister of Petroleum]]|years=2013\u2013present|after=Incumbent}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Rouhani cabinet}}\n{{Khatami cabinet}}\n{{Iran Petroleum Ministers}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zangeneh, Bijan Namdar}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of Tehran alumni]]\n[[Category:Iranian Vice Ministers]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Iran]]\n[[Category:Oil ministers of Iran]]\n[[Category:Executives of Construction Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Iranian people of Kurdish descent]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=August 2013}}\n{{Infobox President \n| name         = Bijan Namdar Zangeneh\n| image        = Bijan Namdar Zangeneh 2019 (cropped).jpg\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1952|9|21|df=y}}<ref>[https://www.opec.org/opec_web/static_files_project/media/downloads/about_us/IR%20Iran.pdf Eng. Bijan Namdar Zanganeh]</ref>\n| birth_place  = [[Kermanshah]], [[Iran]]\n| order        = [[Ministry of Petroleum (Iran)|Minister of Petroleum]]\n| term_start   = 15 August 2013\n| term_end     = \n| deputy       = [[Kazem Vaziri Hamaneh]]<br>[[Marzieh Shah-Daei]]\n| president    = [[Hassan Rouhani]]\n| predecessor  = [[Rostam Ghasemi]]\n| order2       = \n| term_start2  = 14 August 1997\n| term_end2    = 7 August 2005\n| president2   = [[Mohammad Khatami]]\n| predecessor2 = [[Gholam Reza Aghazadeh]]\n| successor2   = [[Kazem Vaziri Hamane]]\n| order3       = [[Ministry of Energy (Iran)|Minister of Energy]]\n| term_start3  = 2 September 1988\n| term_end3    = 14 August 1997\n| president3   = [[Ali Khamenei]]<br>[[Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani]]\n| primeminister3 = [[Mir-Hossein Mousavi]]\n| predecessor3 = [[Abolhassan Khamoushi]] {{small|(Acting)}}\n| successor3   = [[Habibollah Bitaraf]]\n| order4       = [[Jihad of Construction|Minister of Jihad of Construction]]\n| term_start4  = 14 November 1983\n| term_end4    = 2 September 1988\n| president4   = [[Ali Khamenei]]\n| primeminister4 = [[Mir-Hossein Mousavi]]\n| predecessor4 = ''Office established''\n| successor4   = [[Gholamreza Forouzesh]]\n| party        = [[Executives of Construction Party]]\n| alma_mater   = [[University of Tehran]] \n| occupation   = \n| spouse       = \n| children     = 4<ref>[http://www.tasnimnews.com/fa/news/1392/05/14/111787/%D8%B3%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%82-%D9%88-%DA%A9%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%85%D9%87-%D8%A8%DB%8C%DA%98%D9%86-%D9%86%D8%A7%D9%85%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%B1-%D8%B2%D9%86%DA%AF%D9%86%D9%87-%DA%A9%D9%87-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%AD%D8%A7%D9%86%DB%8C-%D8%B1%D9%88%D8%B2-%DA%AF%D8%B0%D8%B4%D8%AA%D9%87-%D8%A8%D9%87-%D9%85%D8%AC%D9%84%D8%B3-%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%AF \u0633\u0648\u0627\u0628\u0642 \u0648 \u06a9\u0627\u0631\u0646\u0627\u0645\u0647 \"\u0628\u06cc\u0698\u0646 \u0646\u0627\u0645\u062f\u0627\u0631 \u0632\u0646\u06af\u0646\u0647\" \u06a9\u0647 \u0631\u0648\u062d\u0627\u0646\u06cc \u0631\u0648\u0632 \u06af\u0630\u0634\u062a\u0647 \u0628\u0647 \u0645\u062c\u0644\u0633 \u062f\u0627\u062f ]</ref>\n| signature    = Bijan Namdar Zanganeh signature.svg\n| signature_alt= \n}}\n'''Bijan Namdar Zangeneh''' ({{lang-fa|\u0628\u064a\u0698\u0646 \u0646\u0627\u0645\u062f\u0627\u0631 \u0632\u0646\u06af\u0646\u0647}}; born 21 September 1952) is an [[Iranian peoples|Iranian]] politician, who served as minister at different cabinets after the Islamic Revolution for 32 years. He has been serving as oil minister since 15 August 2013 in [[Government of Hassan Rouhani (2013\u2013present)|the cabinet]] led by [[Hassan Rouhani]].\n\n==Early life and education==\nZangeneh was born to a Kurdish family in [[Kermanshah]] in 1951.<ref>http://www.rudaw.net/english/middleeast/iran/21082017</ref> He spent his early school years in his hometown before moving to [[Tehran]] where he received his high school diploma. He received his MSc in civil engineering from the [[University of Tehran]] in 1977 and then became a Civil Engineering professor at [[K. N. Toosi University of Technology]] until his retirement in 2006.<ref>http://dolat.ir/detail/230025 \u062e\u0644\u0627\u0635\u0647 \u0627\u06cc \u0627\u0632 \u0633\u0648\u0627\u0628\u0642 \u0639\u0644\u0645\u06cc \u060c\u0641\u0631\u0647\u0646\u06af\u06cc \u060c\u0633\u06cc\u0627\u0633\u06cc \u0648 \u0627\u062c\u0631\u0627\u06cc\u06cc \u0648\u0632\u06cc\u0631\u0646\u0641\u062a</ref>\n\n==Career and activities==\n[[File:Ali Khamenei visit Karkheh Dam (5).jpg|thumb|left|Namdar Zanganeh (right) as minister of energy  with [[Ali Khamenei]], visiting [[Karkheh Dam]], 14 March 1997.]]\nFollowing the [[1979 revolution]], Zangeneh was appointed deputy for the minister of culture and Islamic guidance in 1980.<ref name=sara>{{cite web|title=Iran's Oil Minister Confronts Sanctions|url=http://www.atlanticcouncil.org/publications/articles/iran-s-oil-minister-confronts-sanctions|publisher=Atlantic Council|accessdate=13 September 2013|author=Sara Vakhshouri |date=21 August 2013}}</ref> In 1983, he was made minister of construction jihad.<ref name=sara /> He was appointed minister of energy in the government of [[Mir-Hossein Mousavi]] in 1988.<ref name=sara /> He also served as the energy minister in [[Akbar Hashemi Rafsanjani]]'s cabinet<ref name=cabinet>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1997/08/21/world/iranian-parliament-approves-moderate-president-s-new-cabinet.html|title=Iranian Parliament Approves Moderate President's New Cabinet|accessdate=24 January 2010|date=21 August 1997|work=The New York Times}}</ref> and made massive efforts for reconstruction and rehabilitation of the country's water and electricity industry in the aftermath of the 1980\u20131988 [[Iran\u2013Iraq War]] and the damages caused to the industry in the Iraqi attacks. He was the minister of petroleum in [[Mohammad Khatami]]'s cabinet.<ref name=cabinet /> Zangeneh was replaced by [[Kazem Vaziri Hamane]] in the post on 29 August 2005 as appointed by President [[Mahmoud Ahmadinejad]].<ref name=sara />\n\nHe was appointed as a member of the [[Expediency Council]] by the [[Supreme Leader]], [[Ayatollah Ali Khamenei]], in 1996. He taught at several universities and academic centers; but he was basically a faculty member at [[K. N. Toosi University of Technology]].\n\nIn early August 2013, Zangeneh was nominated as the petroleum minister by President Rouhani and was confirmed on 15 August.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kamali Dehghan|first=Saeed|title=Iran's parliament approves 15 of Hassan Rouhani's 18 cabinet ministers|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2013/aug/15/iran-middleeast|accessdate=15 August 2013|newspaper=The Guardian|date=15 August 2013}}</ref> On 21 August Zanganeh was named as the head of [[Gas Exporting Countries Forum]] (GECF) for 2013.<ref>{{cite news|title=Iran's Oil Minister Appointed GECF Head|url=http://www.mees.com/en/articles/8276-irans-oil-minister-apointed-gecf-head|accessdate=13 September 2013|work=Mees|date=21 August 2013|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130913153736/http://www.mees.com/en/articles/8276-irans-oil-minister-apointed-gecf-head|archivedate=13 September 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Kazem Vaziri Hamaneh was appointed as Zangeneh's deputy on 3 September.<ref>{{cite news|title=Vaziri-Hamaneh appointed as Iran's deputy oil minister|url=http://www.tehrantimes.com/economy-and-business/110477-vaziri-hamaneh-appointed-as-irans-deputy-oil-minister-|accessdate=13 September 2013|newspaper=Tehran Times|date=3 September 2013|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130913150049/http://www.tehrantimes.com/economy-and-business/110477-vaziri-hamaneh-appointed-as-irans-deputy-oil-minister-|archivedate=13 September 2013|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Bijan Namdar Zanganeh}}\n{{Portal|Iran|Politics|Biography}}\n{{s-start}} \n{{s-off}}\n{{succession box|before=Position established|title=[[Cabinet of Iran|Minister of Agriculture]]|years=1983\u20131988|after=Gholamreza Forouzesh}}\n{{succession box|before=Mohammad-Taqi Banqi|title=[[Cabinet of Iran|Minister of Energy]]|years=1988\u20131997|after=[[Habibollah Bitaraf]]}}\n{{succession box|before=[[Gholam Reza Aghazadeh]]|title=[[Ministry of Petroleum (Iran)|Minister of Petroleum]]|years=1997\u20132005|after=[[Kazem Vaziri Hamane]]}}\n{{succession box|before=[[Rostam Ghasemi]]|title=[[Ministry of Petroleum (Iran)|Minister of Petroleum]]|years=2013\u2013present|after=Incumbent}}\n{{s-end}}\n{{Rouhani cabinet}}\n{{Khatami cabinet}}\n{{Iran Petroleum Ministers}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Zangeneh, Bijan Namdar}}\n[[Category:1951 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:University of Tehran alumni]]\n[[Category:Iranian Vice Ministers]]\n[[Category:Government ministers of Iran]]\n[[Category:Oil ministers of Iran]]\n[[Category:Executives of Construction Party politicians]]\n[[Category:Iranian people of Kurdish descent]]\n", "name_user": "Armin123421", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEarly life and education:correction of year of born.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bijan_Namdar_Zangeneh"}
